cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal verification of a declarative approach to business processes. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses modeling issues in artifact-centric systems. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with data-centric processes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses guidelines for turning an arbitrary GSM model into a state-bounded, verifiable model. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the translation of GSM into a formal framework.
